Musics.title: Classical Music
Musics.description: A timeless form with intricate compositions and orchestral arrangements, classical music spans centuries and features renowned composers like Mozart and Beethoven.

Musics.title: Acoustic Music
Musics.description: Acoustic music relies on natural sound amplification without electronic instruments. It often features unplugged performances using acoustic guitars, pianos, or other non-amplified instruments, highlighting a raw and authentic sound.

Musics.title: Folk Music
Musics.description: Rooted in regional traditions, folk music tells cultural stories using instruments like guitars and fiddles, showcasing global diversity.

Musics.title: Modern Music
Musics.description: Evolving in the 20th and 21st centuries, modern music, including pop, rock, and hip-hop, embraces innovation and reflects contemporary societal themes.

Musics.title: Punjabi Music
Musics.description: Dynamic and diverse, city music, like jazz and hip-hop, captures the urban pulse, reflecting the multicultural vibrancy of village punjabi life.

Musics.title: Traditional Music
Musics.description: Preserving cultural identity, traditional music, passed down through generations, plays a vital role in connecting communities with their heritage.
